---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---
<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words Starting With X — XYLOPHONE, XENON, XEROX & More" description="Rare but powerful Scrabble words starting with X. XYLOPHONE (24pts), XEROX (19pts), XENON (12pts). Strategy for playing X-initial words on premium squares." keywords="scrabble words starting with x, xylophone scrabble, xenon scrabble word, xerox scrabble, x words scrabble, words beginning with x scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words Starting With X — XYLOPHONE, XENON, XEROX & More","description":"Rare but powerful Scrabble words starting with X. XYLOPHONE (24pts), XEROX (19pts), XENON (12pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-starting-with-x"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What Scrabble words start with X?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"High-scoring X-initial words include XYLOPHONE (24pts), XEROX (19pts), XENON (12pts), XI (9pts), XU (9pts), and XYST (11pts). X-starting words are rare but powerful because they immediately deploy the 8-point X tile."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is XEROX a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XEROX is valid in SOWPODS as a verb meaning to photocopy, scoring 19 points (X=8, E=1, R=1, O=1, X=8). It requires both X tiles since it contains two X's — a rare but devastating play."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the shortest words starting with X in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The shortest X-starting words are XI (9pts, a Greek letter) and XU (9pts, a Vietnamese monetary unit). Both are valid in TWL and SOWPODS, scoring 9 points in just 2 letters."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Letter Guides</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Starting With X — XYLOPHONE, XENON, XEROX & More</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Words starting with X are among the rarest in Scrabble — but they're disproportionately powerful. The X tile is worth 8 points, and leading with it means you're guaranteeing that premium value lands on the board. From the 2-letter XI to the 9-letter XYLOPHONE, X-initial words reward players who memorise them.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">24 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">XYLOPHONE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">19 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">XEROX</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">XENON</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">XI / XU</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top X-Starting Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎵 XYLOPHONE — 24 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X(8)+Y(4)+L(1)+O(1)+P(3)+H(4)+O(1)+N(1)+E(1). 9 letters, bingo-eligible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📠 XEROX — 19 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X(8)+E(1)+R(1)+O(1)+X(8). Uses BOTH X tiles. SOWPODS valid.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚗️ XENON — 12 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X(8)+E(1)+N(1)+O(1)+N(1). Chemical element. Simple tiles after X.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔤 XI / XU — 9 pts each</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">2-letter X words. XI = Greek letter. XU = Vietnamese currency. Both TWL valid.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why X-Starters Matter</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Positional Control</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Most players think of X as a mid-word or end-word letter (AX, OX, WAX). But starting with X gives you <span class="text-white font-medium">positional control</span> — you choose exactly where the 8-point tile lands, rather than reacting to board opportunities.</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More X-Starting Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">XYST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">XYLEM</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">17 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">XERIC</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">XENIAL</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13 pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">XEBEC</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16 pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for X-Starting Plays</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">XI and XU are emergency plays:</span> When the board is tight and you can't find a spot for X, these 2-letter words score 9 points and fit virtually anywhere. They also create excellent cross-word scoring opportunities.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">XYST is an underused gem:</span> Meaning a garden walk, XYST scores 11 points in 4 letters with no vowels except the implied Y. It's perfect for consonant-heavy racks and fits tight board positions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">XYLOPHONE is a bingo dream:</span> At 9 letters, it needs 2 tiles on the board — but scores 24 base points plus the 50-point bonus. If the board has common extensions, you might reach it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/8-letter-words-with-x/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">8-Letter Words With X — Bingo Territory</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words in Scrabble — Complete Guide</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-starting-with-z/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Starting With Z — ZEPHYR, ZENITH & More</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
